<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">867.48/1157: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-23"><hi rend="italic">January 23,
                                    1919</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 3.18
                                p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>6893. Your telegram 6997, 16th, repeated from London relative to despatch
                            of three relief ships to Turkey.<note n="15" xml:id="d801fn15"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note> Foreign Office states that
                            desired facilities will be given to the vessels and necessary
                            instructions issued to French High Commissioners at Constantinople and
                            Beirut.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bliss</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>